{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2b04bdde-12b7-4c6d-96ee-5ff7cbce3428","content":"Neither — use **`dotnet watch`** to benefit from hot reload.\n\n- `dotnet watch test` — re-runs tests automatically when files change.\n- `dotnet watch run` — restarts/hot-reloads an app on changes.\n\n`dotnet test` and `dotnet run` execute once and exit; they don't watch for file changes. The `watch` command is what triggers hot reload.\n\nFor a test project like yours, run:\n\n```\ndotnet watch test\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c1957b2a-a43f-449d-b0a2-2b329838ee49","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET hot reload and whether to use `dotnet test` or `dotnet run`. Let me look at the project files to understand the context.","outputTokens":166,"requestId":"CFDC:131578:1599941:1913FF5:69EC197B"},"id":"ffd9e70f-5376-45c6-b85c-5dd19676fdaf","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:31:44.708Z","parentId":"ff2b7ddc-1fa7-406c-ac79-d543b84d155f"}
